material.mattext: The sequential logic structure allows decisions to be made.
The problem analysis chart, the IPO chart, the structure chart, the algorithms, and the flowchart are all tools to be used in the development of a solution to a problem.
The algorithm and the flowchart are the same thing.
The equals sign in an assignment statement really means equals to.
The word end and exit can be used interchangeably according to the desire of the developer.
The Return instruction is used to end a module.
The Return instruction and the Exit instruction are exactly the same and can be used interchangeably.
An instruction has two parts: the general instruction followed by the specifications on how to execute the instruction.
In a coupling diagram, all variables are indicated in the same way.
It is not important to indicate what documentation is needed as you are developing the solution.
The flattened ellipse in a flowchart indicates:
The start or stop of the module.

The interactivity (structure) chart is developed by:
Using the similar types of modules for all programs.
Breaking the total solution into functional parts called modules.
Placing the names and numbers of the modules in rectangles which are then placed on the chart in a hierarchical fashion to show which modules process which other ones.
Written to clarify the logic of the program.
Of the several problem solving tools introduced, which provides the BEST view of the program logic in two-dimensions.
Of the several problem solving tools introduced, which provides the BEST view of the pseudocode
Of the several problem solving tools introduced, which provides the BEST view of the alternative solutions
May be used with other logic structures.
Is used is almost all solutions.
Concludes with a return, an end, or an exit.
Separates the data from the required results from the required processing when identifying the problem.
Designates the modules in which the individual processing is completed.
Gives a graphic representation of the solution.
Designates the data type of each piece of data used in the solution.
Designates any pseudonyms of each piece of data.
Designates the scope of the data.
In the development of a solution:
The IPO chart is developed first.
The algorithms and flowcharts are developed together.

Parameters, local variables, and module number.
The value of return through the name of the module.
Return values of the call-by-value parameters.
